The paper discusses a learning algorithm for unsupervised feature finding and deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of high-level representation data in the form of unlabeled categories suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of sparse coding when applied to non-Gaussian data, which suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the proposed algorithm for solving L1-regularized convex optimization suggests information theory (cs.IT) as a possible sub-category.
